Review Comment:
   The spacing is odd because it's trying to make a grid, so the start of `"string"` is aligned with the end of `"number_or_string"` on the next line.
   
   FWIW, the preference I have acquired since writing this is to include a trailing comma in any array literal which will span multiple lines. `clang-format` recognizes this and puts each element on its own line, which looks much cleaner to me.



